pg| ***** 27 ***** |


at|
As this is a notrump contest, South should have the @hJ108 or @hJ109.  
Since North can see the @H8 in dummy, she should place partner with the J109x(x).  
To make sure the heart suit doesn’t block, she wants to play the @HQ at trick 1.  
By the way, the opening leads I recommend are what are called "coded" Jacks, 10's and 9's 
(please check Kantar's books on defense for a complete explanation of coded leads).
Basically, the lead of the J is top of a sequence and it denies a higher honor.|
