at|mitche: The lead of the 10 or 9 is either the top of a sequence or  HJ^*u10^*n(x), or from H10^*u9^*n(x) 
It implies the next higher honor and a third, NON-Touching higher honor, e.g. KJ10xx leads the 10.  But QJ10xx leads the Q.

The old-fashioned (and still considered standard lead) is top of an interior sequence, e.g. the @HJ from @hKJ10xx.  
This puts third hand in a genuine quandary in some situations.  
So we would like to use coded leads and for North to play the @HQ.|
