at|CarlieG:  What values or holdings are needed to balance at the 2 level  vul and n/v?
mitche:  Points are less important than shape for balancing.  When the opponents stop at the 2 level, they probably 
have at most 22-23 HCP, meaning your side has 17-18.  
And if that's so, you can safely play at the 2-level in an 8-card fit.  Balancing is much easier when you are fortunate 
enough to have spades, because you can outbid the opps at the same level.  Which is why Spades are known 
informally as "the boss suit" or "God's suit" (if you are either very reverant or very irreverant).|
